---
import BaseLink from "@/components/common/BaseLink.astro";
import Prose from "@/components/common/Prose.astro";
import SimplePageLayout from "@/layouts/SimplePageLayout.astro";
import { links, site } from "@/lib/site";

const updated = "2026-07-14";
---

<SimplePageLayout
  title="Privacy"
  eyebrow="Legal"
  description={`How the ${site.name} marketing site handles data.`}
>
  <Prose>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">
      Last updated: {updated}. This is a lightweight policy for a static marketing
      site. It is not a substitute for counsel-reviewed legal advice.
    </p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
      The {site.name} marketing website is a <strong>static site</strong>. For
      the current release (v1 of this site):
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        We do <strong>not</strong> use analytics cookies or third-party tracking
        scripts.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do <strong>not</strong> run advertising pixels or session-replay tools.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do <strong>not</strong> collect accounts, profiles, or form
        submissions through this website.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What this site is</h2>
    <p>
      This site describes the {site.name} CLI and links to the open-source
      repository and documentation. It is hosted as static files (for example on
      GitHub Pages). Visiting the site may cause your browser to request those
      files from the host’s infrastructure.
    </p>

    <h2>Server and infrastructure logs</h2>
    <p>
      Hosting providers and CDNs (such as GitHub Pages) may automatically process
      standard request data, including IP address, user agent, timestamps, and
      requested URLs, for security, reliability, and abuse prevention. That processing is
      controlled by the host’s policies, not by application-level trackers we
      install.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      Links to GitHub, npm, or other third-party sites are subject to those
      parties’ privacy practices. We do not control cookies or tracking on
      external sites you choose to open.
    </p>

    <h2>The Astro Stack CLI</h2>
    <p>
      The CLI runs on <strong>your machine</strong>. Project generation writes
      files to a directory you choose. The marketing site does not receive your
      project configuration or source code through the website.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If we add analytics or other data collection later, we will update this
      page before enabling it and describe what is collected and why.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For project-related questions, use the{" "}
      <BaseLink href={links.github} external>
        GitHub repository
      </BaseLink>
      {" "}
      (issues or discussions as available).
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p>
      <BaseLink href="legal/terms/">Terms of use</BaseLink>
      {" · "}
      <BaseLink href="/">Home</BaseLink>
    </p>
  </Prose>
</SimplePageLayout>
